# SDUI Computed & Search Param Sync

## Computed Runner — Generic Operations Only

**Rule:** `lib/sdui/computed-runner.ts` must only define **generic, parameterized** operations. No domain-specific logic (e.g. product, variant, collection).

**Use these generic ops in `config/store.json` computed:**

| Operation | Purpose | Example |
|------------|---------|---------|
| `findItemById` | Find item in array by id field | `{ "findItemById": [{ "var": "product.variants" }, { "var": "product.selectedVariantId" }] }` |
| `findItemByOptionsMatch` | Find item whose options match selectedOptions | `{ "findItemByOptionsMatch": [variants, optionGroups, selectedOptions] }` |
| `findFirstByPreference` | Find first item where preferPath exists, else first; return valuePath | `{ "findFirstByPreference": [{ "var": "product.collections" }] }` |
| `filterExcludeByFieldAndSlice` | Filter where item[field] !== value, slice to limit | `{ "filterExcludeByFieldAndSlice": [items, "productId", excludeValue, 12] }` |
| `getFromMap` | Lookup key in map (returns null if not found) | `{ "getFromMap": [{ "var": "product.selectedOptions" }, { "var": "$parent.id" }] }` |
| `lookupMap` | Lookup key in map with default | `{ "lookupMap": [map, key, defaultVal] }` |
| `lookupInArray` | Find item by key field, return display field | `{ "lookupInArray": [arr, keyField, keyValue, returnField] }` |
| `at` | Get item at index | `{ "at": [arr, index] }` |
| `paginationPages` | Page numbers with ellipsis | `{ "paginationPages": [totalItems, skip, pageSize, delta?] }` |

**Never use:** `findVariantById`, `findMatchingVariantId`, `primaryCollectionSlug`, `filterRelatedProducts`, `selectedOptionForGroup` — these were removed; use the generic equivalents above.

**When adding new computed logic:** Add a generic op with configurable params (field paths, keys, limits) in `computed-runner.ts`, then use it in `store.json`. Never hardcode app-specific field names in the runner.

**One-off action values:** For derived values used only in a single action (e.g. checkout step sync), use inline `{ "expr": "..." }` or `{ "var": "path" }` in the action config—do not add to `store.json` computed. Use `store.json` computed only for values reused across multiple places (text, conditions, several actions).

